title: Signing of the African free-trade deal - Xolelwa Mlumbi-Peter
description:
The South African government says it still has to consult relevant stakeholders before signing the African free-trade deal.
President Cyril Ramaphosa says government needs more time to do it. The president did not sign the agreement at the African Union Extraordinary Summit in Rwanda. He only signed the declaration on the establishment of the African Continental Free Trade Area. 
For me, on we are joined from our Pretoria studios the deputy director general for International Trade and Economic development at the DTI - Xolelwa Mlumbi-Peter.

For more news, visit: sabcnews.com
